%spark2.pyspark
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

fig_size = plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"]
fig_size[0] = 30
fig_size[1] = 5
plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = fig_size

for data in result:
    datesMeasurement, measurement = data.buildMeasurementData()
    datesError, error = data.buildErrorData()
    datesAnomaly, anomaly = data.buildAnomalyData()
    datesTrashHold, anomalyTrashHold = data.buildAnomalyTrashholdData()
    datesPrediction, prediction = data.buildPredictionData()
    
    plt.figure()
    ax1 = plt.subplot2grid((2, 2), (0, 0), colspan=1)
    ax1.plot(datesMeasurement, measurement, linestyle="-", color="green", linewidth=0.7)
    ax1.plot(datesTrashHold, anomalyTrashHold, linestyle="None", marker="o", markerfacecolor="None", markersize=10, color="red")
    ax1.grid()
    
    ax2 = plt.subplot2grid((2, 2), (0, 1), colspan=1)
    ax2.plot(datesMeasurement, measurement, linestyle="-", color="green", linewidth=0.7)
    ax2.plot(datesError, error, linestyle="-", color="red", linewidth=0.7)
    ax2.grid()
    
    ax3 = plt.subplot2grid((2, 2), (1, 0), colspan=1)
    ax3.plot(datesMeasurement, measurement, linestyle="-", color="green", linewidth=0.7)
    ax3.plot(datesAnomaly, anomaly, linestyle="-", color="blue", linewidth=0.7)
    ax3.grid()
    
    ax4 = plt.subplot2grid((2, 2), (1, 1), colspan=1)
    ax4.plot(datesMeasurement, measurement, linestyle="-", color="green", linewidth=0.7)
    ax4.plot(datesPrediction, prediction, linestyle="-", color="brown", linewidth=0.7)
    ax4.grid()
